  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>You are used to throwing things you have on hand.</em><br /><br /><strong>Benefits</strong><br />You do not suffer any penalties for using an improvised ranged weapon. You receive a +1 circumstance bonus on attack rolls made with thrown splash weapons.<br /><br /><strong>Normal</strong><br />You take a -4 penalty on attack rolls made with an improvised weapon.<br /><br /><strong>Combat Trick</strong><br />As long as you have at least 1 stamina point in your stamina pool, when you use a melee weapon that is not a thrown weapon for a ranged improvised weapon attack, you use the weapon's melee critical threat range and multiplier instead of the normal 20/ x2 for improvised weapons. You can spend 2 stamina points to increase your range increment for thrown weapon attacks (including ranged improvised weapons) by 10 feet until the beginning of your next turn.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Usage</strong>: add manually +1 to splash weapons attacks.</p>",
